                                                                    <article id="page-6217" class="row-fluid post-6217 page type-page status-publish has-post-thumbnail czr-hentry"><header class="entry-header"><h1 class="entry-title ">COVID-19 Updates</h1>
<hr class="featurette-divider __before_content"></header><div class="entry-content">
          
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img src="https://khalsamontessori.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/COVID-19Banner2-1024x361.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-6232"></figure></div>



<h4> <em>Updates regarding the Khalsa Montessori response to COVID-1</em>9 </h4>



<p> Khalsa has an important role in slowing the spread of this disease. Information about this situation is rapidly evolving, and we are in close communication with the Maricopa County Department of Public Health, ADHS, and the Department of Ed. </p>



<p>Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman have officially closed all Arizona schools through the end of the 2019-20 school year. Link to  <a href="https://www.azed.gov/communications/2020/03/10/guidance-to-schools-on-covid-19/">Communication Statement</a> from the Governor. Khalsa school will be closed until 5/29/20. Vacation Care is also unavailable at this time </p>



<h4 class="has-vivid-red-color has-text-color">As of today, 3/30/20 we will be closed until 5/29/20 as ordered by Governor Ducey. Vacation Care is not available at this time.</h4>



<p>Please check back to this page regularly as we will be using it to communicate updates as more information is made available. </p>



<p>We are carefully monitoring directives from county health authorities who have provided guidance that schools take steps to reduce gatherings of large public groups and increase social distancing. </p>



<p>For more information on how you can prevent the spread of the coronavirus, follow this <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/downloads/workplace-school-and-home-guidance.pdf">link</a> to the <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-nCoV/index.html">CDC website</a>.</p>
